{
  "texts": [
    "Have there been interventions to increase growth or development of these tools, such as commercialization or scaling up of labs?",
    "3 Yes, there are major interventions which are likely to substantially increase growth or tool development.",
    "Scaling, acquisition and collaboration to exploit compute and data resources for AI-enabled small biomolecule design appear very widespread in the pharmaceutical industry, although there are no public indicators to assess this.",
    "There are strong incentives for continued commercialisation and rapid scale-up of systems for generating training data and developing new models.",
    "The UK has a Medicines Discovery Catapult, although this has not dedicated much attention to supporting AI-enabled design."
  ]
}